Rating: 4
This is a delicious as well as an easy recipe. It works equally as well as a weekday recipe (just make the sauce ahead of time) or an impressive dish for company. I love how forgiving this recipe is. If you don't like fennel, just double the onion. Good fresh tomatoes available? Just chop some up and throw them in the sauce. If you leave it in the oven a few minutes too long, no big deal; unlike other fish recipes, because of the tomato sauce, the fish doesn't dry out if it is a bit overdone. I always bake the fish flat rather than bother with rolling up the filets. Any white fleshed fish works just as well, including cod or tilapia. If you dip the filets in whisked egg, the bread crumbs adhere better. Really good in the summer with a side of corn pudding or sauteed corn.

